Episodes.Title: Day 5: 7:00 A.M.-8:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
18 months have passed since the events of Day 4. With the exception of David Palmer, Tony Almeida, Michelle Dessler and Chloe O'Brian, the world believes that Jack Bauer is dead. Jack is living near L.A. under the name of Frank Flynn, working on an oil rig and living with Diane Huxley and her teenage son, Derek.

In L.A., David Palmer is visiting his brother Wayne, when he is killed by an assassin's bullet. As CTU scrambles to gather more information, an exploding car bomb kills Michelle and inj
Episodes.GuestStars: Eric Winzenried,  Michael Jacey,  John Beard,  Kevin Scott Allen,  Eddie Mekka,  Jeff Kober,  Dennis Haysbert

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 8:00 A.M.-9:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack and Chloe infiltrate Wayne Palmer's penthouse where David Palmer was assassinated, in the hopes of finding a clue to his murder. Jack convinces Wayne to cooperate and finds some information in Palmer's memoirs that leads him to the airport where the Russian president is about to land. 

CTU and Secret Service attempt to capture Jack, but they only find Chloe as Jack and Derek slip through their grasp. 

Martha tries to convince her husband that she received an important phone call from Palm
Episodes.GuestStars: Kevin E. West,  David Dayan Fisher,  Matt Battaglia,  Elizabeth Espinoza,  Musashi Alexander,  Taras Los

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 9:00 A.M.-10:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack conceals himself inside the airport hanger and surveys the Russian separatists, feeding information to Curtis and his assault team. 

The terrorists begin executing hostages in an attempt to make Logan cave into their demands. 

Martha discovers that all traces of her conversation with Palmer may not have been erased.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Gleeson Connolly,  V.J. Foster,  David Dayan Fisher,  Taylor Nichols,  Steve Edwards,  Taras Los,  Joey Munguia,  Reggie Jordan,  Lou Richards,  Karla Zamudio

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 10:00 A.M.-11:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack is captured by the terrorists, who use Derek as leverage to force him to compromise CTU's assault operation. 

Logan refuses to give into the terrorist demands as the time of the co-signing of the treaty draws near. Martha tries to tell her husband of the evidence she uncovered about her phone call with Palmer, but Walt interferes with her efforts. 

A new representative from District arrives at CTU and begins to undermine Buchanan's authority.
Episodes.GuestStars: David Joyner,  Michael Roddy,  Jerad Anderson,  Mark Henderson,  Steve Edwards,  V.J. Foster,  David Dayan Fisher,  Marci Michelle,  Roman Varshavsky,  Mark  Thompson,  Kathleen Gati

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 11:00 A.M.-12:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack returns to CTU and has an emotional reunion with Audrey, while Curtis tracks the Russians and the stolen nerve gas. 

Walt sends in a hit man to silence Jack. 

Chloe discovers that Spencer has his own agenda at CTU. 

Walt convinces Logan to have Martha institutionalized when she tells them of the attack on her.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R16 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Roman Varshavsky,  Robert Rusler,  Josie Di Vincenzo,  Timothy V. Murphy,  Eric Strikland,  Tim Edward Rhoze,  Glenn Morshower,  Alex Castillo,  Blaine Pate,  Robb Reesman,  Michael Roddy

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 12:00 P.M.-1:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack contacts Mike and asks for a secret meeting in hopes of gathering evidence against Walt. 

Martha begs Aaron for help, while a desperate Walt tries to force Logan to aid him in his complicity with the terrorists. 

Buchanan butts heads with Lynn over a decision to violate the president's orders, while the Russians attempt to escape with the nerve gas.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R16 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Benjamin Parrillo,  Timothy V. Murphy,  Brady Corbet,  Connie Britton,  Michael Karawia,  Terry Woodberry,  Michael Yavnieli,  Matt Huhn,  Anita Finlay

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 1:00 P.M. - 2:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack tracks down a man who has a connection to the terrorists. Logan is forced to grant him immunity in exchange for information on their whereabouts. 

Mike and Martha argue over Logan's public response to Walt's involvement with the Russians. 

Lynn is drawn away from his post by a personal crisis as the terrorists come closer to striking against the U.S.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R16 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Channon Roe,  Patrick Bauchau,  Jonah Lotan,  Kevin Sizemore,  Matthew Boylan,  Scott Vance,  J. David Shanks,  Angela Sarafyan,  Penny Balfour

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 2:00 P.M. - 3:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack poses as Rossler and manages to trace one of the canisters of nerve gas, but he goes against orders from the president when the terrorists target a shopping mall. 

Logan and Martha quarrel when she learns of her husband's intention to cover up the real reason for Walt's suicide.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R16 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Herman Chaves,  Jay Gordon,  Timothy Omundson,  Alla Korot

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 3:00 P.M. - 4:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Lynn orders Curtis to take Jack into custody for violating presidential orders, but Jack breaks away from Curtis when Nathanson contacts him through Audrey and offers information on the location of the nerve gas.

Lynn begins to unleash on his coworkers as he discovers that they may be working against him to aid Jack.

The head of the terrorists makes a demand on Logan, and Martha takes a dangerous step to get her husband's attention.
Episodes.GuestStars: Geraint Wyn Davies,  Tony Wayne,  Matt Huhn,  Terrence Wayne,  Alex Kuznetsov,  Matthew Boylan,  Anita Finlay,  Penny Balfour,  Mark A. Sheppard

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 4:00 P.M. - 5:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Logan wrestles with his conscience when he learns that Martha is riding in the motorcade with the Suvarovs. 

Audrey convinces Curtis to take action as Lynn continues to abuse his authority. 

Jack learns that an ex CTU agent, Christopher Henderson, works for a company which is connected with the nerve gas.
Episodes.GuestStars: Pia Artesona,  Danielle Burgio,  Sky Soleil,  Alex Kuznetsov

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 5:00 P.M. - 6:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack interrogates Henderson's wife about her husband's connection to the terrorists. 

Lynn begs his sister to return his stolen keycard, while Tony regains consciousness and learns of Michelle's fate. 

Martha gives Logan the cold shoulder, while Curtis tracks another nerve gas attack to a local hospital.
Episodes.GuestStars: Alex Kuznetsov,  Jay Acovone,  Matthew Boylan,  Marat Oyvetsky,  Angelo Perez,  Thomas Vincent Kelly,  Penny Balfour,  JoBeth Williams

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 6:00 P.M. - 7:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack takes Henderson to CTU for questioning. Once there, he faces an unhappy reunion with his daughter, Kim. 

Mike appeals to Martha for help as Logan faces pressure from his Vice-President to declare martial law on L.A. 

Lynn connects the theft of his keycard to an impending strike on CTU, but his warning comes too late to stop a terrorist from infiltrating the building.
Episodes.GuestStars: Alex Kuznetsov,  Danielle Burgio,  C. Thomas Howell,  Dan Warner,  Elisha Cuthbert

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 7:00 P.M. - 8:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack and Lynn must take action when they discover that the nerve gas is breaking through the protective seals that are keeping the CTU survivors alive. 

Chloe wrestles with her grief over Edgar's death, while Tony contemplates revenge against Henderson. 

Martha bolster's Logan's spirit as he wavers under more political pressure from Gardner.
Episodes.GuestStars: Peter Holden,  Martin A. Papazian,  Yorgo Constantine,  Elisha Cuthbert,  Thomas Vincent Kelly,  Stana Katic,  C. Thomas Howell,  Henry Ian Cusick

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 8:00 P.M. - 9:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack bargains with a German intelligence agent in order to find the woman who can lead him to Bierko. 

Buchanan chafes against the new chain of command as Homeland Security prepares to take over CTU operations. 

Aaron receives a request for a secret meeting from Wayne Palmer, as Logan implements martial law in L.A.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Griffin,  Tim  Talman,  Stana Katic,  Yorgo Constantine,  Anita Finlay,  Henry Ian Cusick

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 9:00 P.M. - 10:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack pushes Audrey for answers when evidence indicates that she may be involved with the terrorists. 

Wayne and Aaron flee from a group of gunmen who have orders from Henderson to kill them. 

Bierko and his men gain access to a natural gas plant, where they plan to distribute the nerve gas throughout L.A.
Episodes.GuestStars: Frank Silva,  Christopher Amitrano,  Matthew Jones,  Matt Huhn,  Yorgo Constantine,  Martin A. Papazian,  Stana Katic,  Tohoru Masamune,  Brett Rickaby

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 10:00 P.M. - 11:00 P.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack and Wayne locate a source inside Logan's administration who has information on Palmer's assassination. But things get complicated when they learn that Henderson is using leverage to keep her silent. 

Audrey is forced to choose between Chloe and Buchanan as Homeland Security begins to absorb CTU.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kevin Sizemore,  Skylar Roberge,  Christopher Amitrano,  Jenny Levine

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 11:00 P.M. - 12:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
Jack and Wayne locate a recording that definitively proves Logan's involvement in the terrorist conspiracy, but Henderson corners them in the hopes of destroying the incriminating tape. 

Logan tries to cover his tracks by issuing a warrant for Jack's arrest. 

Audrey contacts her father for help, while Chloe gives her cover while helping Jack evade CTU.
Episodes.GuestStars: William Devane,  Jenny Levine,  Skylar Roberge,  Jason Grutter,  Addie Daddio,  Jeff Campbell,  Jorge Noa,  Rick Garcia,  Brandon Ford Green,  John Posey

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 12:00 A.M. - 1:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Jack shows Heller the incriminating recording in the hopes that he will help them take down Logan, but Heller has plans of his own that will save face for the presidency. Miles tricks Chloe into leading CTU to Jack and Audrey. Mike and Martha both become more suspicious of Logan's actions, while Heller confronts the president with an ultimatum.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mark Thompson,  Jason Grutter,  Larkin Campbell,  Ray Wise,  William Devane

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 1:00 A.M. - 2:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Jack captures Henderson and attempts to force him to hand over the recording, but Henderson targets Heller to buy himself more time. Logan confesses his involvement in Palmer's assassination to a distraught Martha. Miles traces Chloe to Buchanan's home, but Hayes finds herself questioning Logan's motives as CTU closes in.
Episodes.Writer: Craig Van Sickle, Steven Long Mitchell
Episodes.GuestStars: Tracy Howe,  Jenny Levine,  William Devane,  Bernard K. Addison,  Adam Donshik,  Carl Gilliard,  Marc Raducci

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 2:00 A.M. - 3:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot:
After stowing away aboard the flight containing Henderson's contact and the incriminating recording, Jack finds himself having to deal with a pilot who refuses to cooperate.

Martha begins to break down, and Mike becomes suspicious of what she is hiding from him, while Logan tries to calm his financial backers.
Episodes.GuestStars: Aleksandra Kaniak,  Lissa Pallo,  Keith Pillow,  Perry Kelly,  Aaron MacPherson,  Philip Lester,  Tracy Howe,  David Batiste,  Stephanie Erb,  Blake Robbins,  Andrew Hawkes,  Kirk B.R. Woller,  Richard Gilliland

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 3:00 A.M. - 4:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Jack searches for a safe place to land the plane when Logan gives orders to shoot it down. Hayes readies Bierko for a transfer to a secure facility, while Audrey receives some good news about her father. Logan becomes desperate as his plans start to unravel, but an unexpected ally at CTU turns the tables in his favor.
Episodes.GuestStars: Eric Steinberg,  Andrew Hawkes,  Pancho Demmings,  Stephanie Erb,  Jenny Levine,  Tom Wright

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 4:00 A.M. - 5:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Bierko escapes from the transport taking him to Division and uses his last canister of nerve gas for a surprise strike. Jack is forced to work with Henderson to find Bierko, but Henderson wants something in return. Logan takes drastic steps to deal with Aaron when he won't go along with the cover-up.
Episodes.GuestStars: Michael Yavnieli,  Marci Michelle,  Dominic Comperatore,  Clayton Barber,  Eric Steinberg,  Jose Zuniga,  Ravil Isyanov,  Tracy Howe,  Don Fischer

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 5:00 A.M. - 6:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Jack and Henderson wage an assault on the submarine as Bierko prepares to launch an attack against L.A. Chloe brings in someone from her past to aid her. Martha and Aaron enlist Mike's help in their plans to expose Logan.
Episodes.GuestStars: Ravil Isyanov,  Carlo Rota,  Roberto DeCastro,  Peter Weller,  Julian Sands,  Jeremy Ray Valdez,  Tom Wright,  Clayton Barber,  Kate Rene Gleason,  Jayne Atkinson

Episodes.Title: Day 5: 6:00 A.M. - 7:00 A.M.
Episodes.Plot: Jack takes his fight directly to the President as he attempts to force a confession from him that will prove his involvement in the day's events. Martha vents her hatred for her husband in front of the press as Logan gives a eulogy over Palmer's body. Jack and Audrey share a tender moment when it seems the crisis has subsided, but Jack finds that his problems have only begun as his past catches up with him.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tzi Ma,  Christopher Stapleton,  Anita Finlay,  Jack Galle,  Charles Chun,  Sean McGowan,  David Fabrizio,  John Lacy,  Dan Ziskie,  Carlo Rota,  Jayne Atkinson
